result.execSummary:
The defendant Amber Shanice Ellis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Due to not following the payment plan agreement, specifically payment(s) were missed, the payment plan has been ended and the failure to pay action has been enforced.
Assessment for Attorney Fees in the amount of $336.00 entered as ordered by the court on 06/25/2015 to pay $25.00 monthly.  Final payment due by 09/01/2016. Failure to pay is a Civil Judgment.
Affidavit and Order for Payment of Attorney Fees and Costs, signed.

Defendant Amber Shanice Ellis in court with attorney Joel H. Rosenthal.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    
As to Count 2:  Defendant ordered to serve 3 months in the House of Correction consecutive to any other sentence, with Huber Privileges for work, child care, and school.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 2 years with the following conditions:
*15 days of condition time to be used at the agent's discretion. 
*No contact with any TJ Maxx or any Marshalls.
*Full time work and/or school after child is born.
*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*40 hours of community service by 02-16-2016. 
*Paternity must be established within the first 30 days of the birth of the baby. 
*Court WAIVES all costs and non-mandatory surcharges and orders defendant to pay all mandatory surcharges during the term of probation.   If unpaid a civil judgment will be ordered filed against the defendant.

Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.

Defendant Amber Shanice Ellis in court with attorney Joel H. Rosenthal.  Defendant Amber Shanice Ellis in custody.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.

  As to Count 2:  Defendant changes her plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. 

As to Counts 1 and 3:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders Counts 1 and 3 DISMISSED but read-in as to sentencing.

Court orders case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 46.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for June 16, 2015 at 08:30 am.
